      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:39:6",
      "text": [
        " سَمِعْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) يَقُولُ يُقْطَعُ النَّبَّاشُ وَ الطَّرَّارُ وَ لَا يُقْطَعُ الْمُخْتَلِسُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Ja’far Al Kufy, from Muhammad Bin Abdul Hameed, from Sayf Bin Umeyra, from Mansour Bin Hazim who said, ",
          "‘I heard Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> saying: ‘The grave robber, and the pick-pocket would be cut, and the embezzler would not be cut’."
        ]
      }
